Job Description

NYCHHC in New York, NY seeks an ERP Hyperion Developer (Senior Consultant) to serve on a Hyperion Planning team (including the Workforce Planning module) and Profitability and Cost Management modules as well as the Hyperion Data Relationship Management and Essbase configuration.

This position provides functional expertise in identifying and evaluating requirements for the Hyperion and PeopleSoft. This position will provide postproduction support, assist with knowledge transfer activities and help ensure an overall smooth transition process to the new ERP.

Specifically, this position will:
• Provide development and administration support for Hyperion Planning, Profitability and Cost Management and Essbase;
• Develop, Prepare and Review Hyperion Financial Reports;
• Participate in installation of Hyperion EPM environment, configurations and migrations, apply upgrades and patches, and perform data and application back-up and restoration;
• Configure Hyperion to use AD authentication;
• Provide application and Essbase support for Hyperion systems and applications;
• Monitor and optimize system performance;
• Build, Test, Implement and maintenance of Hyperion integration with PeopleSoft Financials, Hospital Revenue Cycle and Other applications;
• Provide internal customers (Finance) with the best possible solutions to utilize Hyperion Budget and Cost Accounting;
• Identify potential process improvements, troubleshoot problems and provide user training and support;
• Evaluate data and serve as the subject matter expert and liaison between Finance, Data Management and EITS teams through the reporting development lifecycle to create reports according to specifications.

Minimum Qualifications
1. Baccalaureate degree from an accredited college or university with a major in Computer Science, Systems Engineering, applied Mathematics, Business Administration, Economics/Statistics, Telecommunications, Data Communications, or a related field of study; and
2. Five (5) years of progressive, responsible experience in the field of data processing, computer systems, and applications. Operations Specialty requires supervisory experience (5 years). Network Services requires a telecommunications background and experience.
3. Broad knowledge and expertise in the characteristics of computers, peripheral devices, communications systems and hardware capabilities, programming languages, E.D.P. applications, systems analysis methodology, data management and retrieval techniques; or
4. A satisfactory equivalent combination of training, education, and experience.

5 years of experience includes data processing, computer systems and applications with the use of software applications for the healthcare sector such as:
• Oracle Hyperion EPM Suite;
• Essbase;
• Shell Scripts, MaxL, MDX;
• EPIC Resolute Hospital Billing;
• Cerner - Unity, Soarian Financials;
• 3M Health Data Management;
• Oracle DRM;
• Oracle SQL, Table, Views, Etc.

If applying online, please include your cover letter in the same file attachment with your uploaded resume.

